{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/334/comments/71431445.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/diff/apojomovsky/ign-transport:90c1bfb7577f..847bd2c7bbd6?path=log%2Fsrc%2FPlayback.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/334/_/diff#comment-71431445"}}, "parent": {"id": 71303150, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/334/comments/71303150.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/334/_/diff#comment-71303150"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 334, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pullrequests/334.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/pull-requests/334"}}, "title": "Added pause/resume to logging"}, "content": {"raw": "Thanks for the feedback, Shane. I completely agree with you about the spurious and the need to check for a predicate. Wouldn't a `wait` with a predicate be enough in this case? IIRC, the `wait_for` is equivalent to a `wait` \\+ a timeout, which is not required in this case.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Thanks for the feedback, Shane. I completely agree with you about the spurious and the need to check for a predicate. Wouldn't a <code>wait</code> with a predicate be enough in this case? IIRC, the <code>wait_for</code> is equivalent to a <code>wait</code> + a timeout, which is not required in this case.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-07-30T16:24:01.334351+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Alexis Pojomovsky", "uuid": "{403b1b93-94af-4398-a283-cf3a3f5deed6}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B403b1b93-94af-4398-a283-cf3a3f5deed6%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B403b1b93-94af-4398-a283-cf3a3f5deed6%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-w